WEBVTT

00:01.523 --> 00:03.003
Previously on
"The Cleaning Lady"...

00:03.046 --> 00:05.179
I asked you not
to involve the FBI.

00:05.222 --> 00:07.224
Mom, he kidnapped Luca.

00:07.268 --> 00:08.617
Why do you keep
defending him?

00:08.660 --> 00:09.661
What do you think
you're doing, huh?

00:09.705 --> 00:10.793
Hey, hey, hey!
Just --

00:10.836 --> 00:12.055
I said, he's asleep.
Just leave --

00:12.099 --> 00:13.056
Let go!

00:13.100 --> 00:14.231
Marco!

00:14.275 --> 00:15.798
[ Bones crack ]

00:15.841 --> 00:17.843
Thony: What happened to Marco
was an accident.

00:17.887 --> 00:20.759
We're not gonna let anything
happen to our family.

00:20.803 --> 00:22.413
The Cortez case was only
taken away from me

00:22.457 --> 00:23.936
because of a technicality.

00:23.980 --> 00:26.983
Sleeping with a CI
is not a technicality.

00:27.027 --> 00:29.768
My lawyer says the judge
can be easily swayed,

00:29.812 --> 00:31.466
so you should be out
by next week.

00:31.509 --> 00:33.250
Judge Tuckerson.
He's corrupt as hell.

00:33.294 --> 00:35.296
We got to stop the bribe
before it happens.

00:35.339 --> 00:36.819
I need to get the hell
out of here.

00:36.862 --> 00:38.473
Arman cut a deal
with the feds.

00:38.516 --> 00:39.996
He's your rat.

00:40.040 --> 00:42.433
Now that I have so many
friends looking out for me,

00:42.477 --> 00:44.087
I know who I can trust

00:44.131 --> 00:45.436
and who I cannot.

00:45.480 --> 00:46.829
[ Grunting ]

00:46.872 --> 00:55.011
♪♪

00:55.055 --> 01:03.150
♪♪

01:03.193 --> 01:11.288
♪♪

01:11.332 --> 01:19.470
♪♪

01:19.514 --> 01:22.995
Female officer:
Everything in the bin, please.

01:23.039 --> 01:24.301
Thank you.

01:24.345 --> 01:25.563
Female officer #2:
Ma'am, over here.

01:25.607 --> 01:27.130
Arms out.

01:27.174 --> 01:29.480
[ Metal detector clicking ]

01:29.524 --> 01:35.617
♪♪

01:35.660 --> 01:41.753
♪♪

01:41.797 --> 01:44.495
You're all set.

01:44.539 --> 01:46.454
[ Buzzer ]

01:46.497 --> 01:49.196
♪♪

01:49.239 --> 01:50.849
Male guard:
Phone number two.

01:50.893 --> 01:53.504
♪♪

01:53.548 --> 01:55.854
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:55.898 --> 02:00.642
♪♪

02:00.685 --> 02:02.513
[ Grunts ]

02:02.557 --> 02:08.867
♪♪

02:08.911 --> 02:15.135
♪♪

02:15.178 --> 02:17.920
Look what they did to you.

02:17.963 --> 02:20.444
What Hayak did.

02:20.488 --> 02:23.186
He sent two guys.

02:23.230 --> 02:24.883
And if I don't
get out of here,

02:24.927 --> 02:26.537
he'll send more
to finish the job.

02:26.581 --> 02:28.104
[ Distant buzzer ]

02:28.148 --> 02:33.979
♪♪

02:34.023 --> 02:39.898
♪♪

02:39.942 --> 02:41.552
Alright, we may have shut down
the Crypto account,

02:41.596 --> 02:44.164
but it's no time
for a victory lap.

02:44.207 --> 02:46.209
Keep your eyes on Nadia Morales.

02:46.253 --> 02:48.211
Make sure she doesn't
tap into funds

02:48.255 --> 02:50.126
that they've got squirreled away
that we don't know about

02:50.170 --> 02:51.432
to bribe the judge.

02:51.475 --> 02:53.085
Oh, there she is.

02:53.129 --> 02:55.000
Miss ASAC Russo, tell me

02:55.044 --> 02:57.177
that Judge Tuckerson
got moved off the case.

02:57.220 --> 03:00.005
Our friends in Public Corruption
got a different idea.

03:00.049 --> 03:02.443
If Morales finds money
for the payoff,

03:02.486 --> 03:04.053
they want it
to change hands.

03:04.096 --> 03:05.359
No.
We can't can't that chance.

03:05.402 --> 03:07.274
If Judge Tuckerson
doesn't get his bribe,

03:07.317 --> 03:09.580
Morales rots in prison.
Done.

03:09.624 --> 03:11.321
Not up to you, Miller.

03:11.365 --> 03:12.931
If we catch Tuckerson
red-handed,

03:12.975 --> 03:17.371
a lot more guys like Arman
will stay behind bars.

03:17.414 --> 03:18.676
Alright.

03:18.720 --> 03:21.244
Well, let's just see
how it plays out.

03:21.288 --> 03:24.682
Stay on 'em, guys.

03:24.726 --> 03:26.945
So, um, you know, once --

03:26.989 --> 03:28.947
once we seal the deal
on this case --

03:28.991 --> 03:30.340
No.

03:30.384 --> 03:31.689
You don't even know
what I have to say.

03:31.733 --> 03:33.082
Come on, Russo.

03:33.125 --> 03:34.736
I know the Cortez case
better than anyone.

03:34.779 --> 03:37.826
Well, as long as Maya's in
with Cortez, you won't be.

03:37.869 --> 03:41.003
Katherine, just get me back in
long enough to get her out.

03:41.046 --> 03:43.832
We owe her that.

03:43.875 --> 03:45.355
I owe her that.

03:45.399 --> 03:46.487
You know in good conscience

03:46.530 --> 03:48.793
I can't put you back
on that case,

03:48.837 --> 03:51.796
but hopefully for me, that'll
soon be someone else's problem.

03:51.840 --> 03:54.364
Yeah, that's right. Still
can't believe you're leaving me.

03:54.408 --> 03:56.279
To run Miami,
of all places.

03:56.323 --> 03:59.978
The promotion's not a done deal,
so don't screw it up for me.

04:00.022 --> 04:03.982
[ Cellphone rings ]

04:04.026 --> 04:06.289
Oh, whoa.
Would you look at that?

04:06.333 --> 04:08.552
Our boy Morales
is back on his feet.

04:08.596 --> 04:10.162
He already has a visitor.

04:10.206 --> 04:11.642
And how's Luca doing?

04:11.686 --> 04:14.297
He doesn't
quite understand.

04:14.341 --> 04:16.995
He keeps
asking for his dad,

04:17.039 --> 04:19.781
so I have to explain it
all over again.

04:19.824 --> 04:21.783
♪♪

04:21.826 --> 04:24.829
How are you holding up?

04:24.873 --> 04:26.570
I feel like
I failed everyone.

04:31.445 --> 04:33.316
Hey, don't blame yourself.

04:33.360 --> 04:38.278
The setback in my case had to do
with a lot of factors.

04:38.321 --> 04:40.192
We don't have
a lot of time to regroup.

04:40.236 --> 04:43.195
So we have to
figure this out now.

04:43.239 --> 04:45.110
I spoke to your team.

04:45.154 --> 04:47.374
You did?

04:47.417 --> 04:48.810
You still have a good case,

04:48.853 --> 04:50.899
but they have to borrow
to pay the higher fees.

04:50.942 --> 04:54.076
Borrow from -- from who?

04:54.119 --> 04:55.730
Someone she knows.

04:55.773 --> 04:57.340
I told her not to do that.

04:57.384 --> 05:00.212
She said it's the only option
with the time you have left.

05:00.256 --> 05:01.562
It's the worst option.

05:01.605 --> 05:04.347
Time's up, Morales.
Say your goodbyes.

05:04.391 --> 05:06.871
[ Buzzer, door opens ]

05:06.915 --> 05:09.091
Just let her do
what she needs to do,

05:09.134 --> 05:10.962
and be careful in here.

05:11.006 --> 05:13.574
That's not how you survive.

05:13.617 --> 05:15.227
[ Receiver clicks ]

05:15.271 --> 05:22.409
♪♪

05:22.452 --> 05:24.149
Female officer:
Here you go.

05:28.589 --> 05:30.068
It's kind of
an odd place to be

05:30.112 --> 05:32.680
when you're about
to bury your husband.

05:32.723 --> 05:33.768
Are you following me?

05:33.811 --> 05:35.204
No. No.

05:35.247 --> 05:37.032
Just got a message
that Arman had a visitor.

05:37.075 --> 05:39.687
Thought I'd see what's up.

05:39.730 --> 05:42.342
I mean, I know
that you had nothing to do

05:42.385 --> 05:43.821
with your husband's death,

05:43.865 --> 05:46.868
but the first suspect
is always the spouse,

05:46.911 --> 05:49.740
especially those
who have friends with reach,

05:49.784 --> 05:51.351
even in prison.

05:51.394 --> 05:53.091
I don't know what you think
he's been doing,

05:53.135 --> 05:55.877
but Arman was
almost beaten to death.

05:55.920 --> 05:57.357
And you let that happen.

05:57.400 --> 05:58.575
Thony, hey,
I can't help it

05:58.619 --> 06:00.969
if the bad guys
take each other out.

06:03.188 --> 06:05.539
Listen, Thony, I mean it.

06:05.582 --> 06:08.629
Doesn't look good,
you being here.

06:08.672 --> 06:10.761
I'm here because Arman
saved my son's life,

06:10.805 --> 06:13.198
and he deserved to know
that he's safe.

06:13.242 --> 06:15.418
If you want to follow me,
I'm on my way to the airport

06:15.462 --> 06:17.507
to pick up Marco's parents
for the funeral.

06:17.551 --> 06:23.861
♪♪

06:23.905 --> 06:30.259
♪♪

06:30.302 --> 06:31.782
Man: [ Over P.A. ] No parking.

06:31.826 --> 06:34.219
Unattended vehicles
will be towed.

06:34.263 --> 06:36.178
Fiona: I just wish Marco
wasn't the reason

06:36.221 --> 06:38.833
Nanayand Tatayare finally
gonna be able to see my kids.

06:38.876 --> 06:41.749
Tatay'sgonna have lots
of questions. Lots of them.

06:41.792 --> 06:44.578
We just have to stick
to the story, Fi.

06:44.621 --> 06:46.231
Marco's wallet
was emptied out.

06:46.275 --> 06:48.408
It looked like
he was mugged.

06:48.451 --> 06:51.411
Even that
sounds awful to say.

06:51.454 --> 06:52.977
I know.

06:53.021 --> 06:57.112
♪♪

06:57.155 --> 07:00.158
[ Voice breaking ]
There they are.

07:00.202 --> 07:03.118
Andito kami. Tay.

07:03.161 --> 07:04.467
Ay.

07:04.511 --> 07:07.165
[ Both crying ]

07:07.209 --> 07:11.474
♪♪

07:11.518 --> 07:14.999
[ Murmuring in Tagalog ]

07:24.531 --> 07:33.365
♪♪

07:33.409 --> 07:36.630
Hello! Look who's here!

07:36.673 --> 07:39.284
Lolo! Lola!

07:39.328 --> 07:41.852
Whoa, look at you!

07:41.896 --> 07:44.115
You've gotten so big!

07:47.249 --> 07:49.469
Oh. Mwah.

07:52.733 --> 07:55.779
Jazmine.
Such a beauty you are.

07:57.912 --> 07:59.870
Ah. And Chris.

08:02.046 --> 08:04.614
You're a young man
already.

08:06.355 --> 08:09.140
Oh.
Ah, good boy, good boy.

08:09.184 --> 08:10.533
Chris: Here. Let me --
Let me get your suitcases.

08:10.577 --> 08:12.187
You guys will be sleeping
in Mom's room, so...

08:13.797 --> 08:15.495
We brought some things.Ooh!

08:15.538 --> 08:17.453
Let me show you.

08:17.497 --> 08:19.063
We weren't sure if the boys

08:19.107 --> 08:20.717
had something to wear
for the funeral.

08:20.761 --> 08:22.545
We brought something.

08:22.589 --> 08:24.721
Oh, uh --

08:24.765 --> 08:28.769
Yeah, Marco was
a little taller than you,

08:28.812 --> 08:31.380
but it'll be okay, huh?
It'll be fine.

08:31.423 --> 08:34.209
[ Drinks pouring ]

08:34.252 --> 08:35.515
[ Speaks Tagalog ]

08:35.558 --> 08:37.560
[ Knock on door ]

08:37.604 --> 08:38.953
I'll get it.

08:41.956 --> 08:44.045
Hello.Thony De La Rosa?

08:44.088 --> 08:45.655
Yes, may I help you?

08:45.699 --> 08:46.917
Detective Lana Flores.

08:46.961 --> 08:48.136
I'm in charge
of the investigation

08:48.179 --> 08:50.268
of the death
of Marco De La Rosa.

08:50.312 --> 08:51.922
I have some questions for you
about you and your husband.

08:51.966 --> 08:53.924
Um, yes, of course.

08:53.968 --> 08:56.623
But, um, my family just arrived
from the Philippines.

08:56.666 --> 09:00.061
Maybe we could talk about this
another time.

09:00.104 --> 09:03.760
If this is about my son,
I want to speak with her.

09:03.804 --> 09:05.457
I want to know
what the police are doing

09:05.501 --> 09:07.329
to find who killed my son.

09:07.372 --> 09:13.988
♪♪

09:18.558 --> 09:20.821
So, you and Marco
were separated?

09:20.864 --> 09:24.041
Well, only because, uh,
I had to bring Luca here

09:24.085 --> 09:26.174
for a bone marrow transplant.

09:26.217 --> 09:28.959
But then, when he came here,
why were he and Luca at a motel

09:29.003 --> 09:30.613
instead of here with you?

09:32.833 --> 09:34.051
We had an argument.

09:34.095 --> 09:37.011
Um, Marco was angry,
so he took Luca.

09:37.054 --> 09:39.317
And that's when you put out
the APB?

09:39.361 --> 09:40.449
Mm-hmm.

09:40.492 --> 09:42.320
Wh-- What is an APB?

09:42.364 --> 09:46.194
It's an alert to inform police
to look for someone.

09:46.237 --> 09:48.892
You tried to
get Marco arrested?

09:48.936 --> 09:51.112
No. I-I-I was just
trying to find Luca.

09:51.155 --> 09:53.810
He was a good father.
He would never hurt his son.

09:53.854 --> 09:55.203
I know.Jacinto, tama na.

09:55.246 --> 09:56.334
Did you think he was
endangering your son?

09:56.378 --> 09:58.554
No.
He was just upset.

10:12.873 --> 10:14.309
Maybe I should come back
at another time?

10:14.352 --> 10:16.006
Yes, please.
Let me see you out.

10:16.050 --> 10:18.008
♪♪

10:18.052 --> 10:19.706
Tingnan mo ang ginawa mo.

10:19.749 --> 10:23.013
♪♪

10:23.057 --> 10:24.449
Flores:
Don't wait too long to call.

10:24.493 --> 10:26.190
Thank you.

10:26.234 --> 10:27.757
I'll call you soon.

10:27.801 --> 10:30.673
♪♪

10:30.717 --> 10:33.894
If she had come back to Manila
when he asked,

10:33.937 --> 10:36.113
he would still be alive.

10:36.157 --> 10:38.986
If -- If she had not called
the police,

10:39.029 --> 10:41.379
he would be alive!

10:41.423 --> 10:44.992
My son would be alive
if it were not for you!

10:45.035 --> 10:46.515
Tay...

10:46.558 --> 10:48.473
♪♪

10:48.517 --> 10:50.171
[ Indistinct conversations ]

10:50.214 --> 10:55.045
♪♪

10:55.089 --> 10:57.657
Don't over-think it.

10:57.700 --> 11:00.050
Roulette is purely
a game of luck.

11:00.094 --> 11:01.704
Like when we first met.

11:01.748 --> 11:04.272
♪♪

11:04.315 --> 11:05.665
Robert.

11:05.708 --> 11:07.754
Nadia.

11:07.797 --> 11:10.017
As stunning as ever.

11:10.060 --> 11:11.235
Please,
don't let me stop you.

11:11.279 --> 11:14.195
I'm not here
to play games, Robert.

11:14.238 --> 11:16.893
I'm just here to talk about --A loan.

11:16.937 --> 11:18.286
I know.

11:18.329 --> 11:21.768
But wouldn't you
rather receive a gift?

11:21.811 --> 11:22.856
A gift?

11:22.899 --> 11:24.422
Place your bet.

11:24.466 --> 11:27.251
If you win,

11:27.295 --> 11:30.777
I'll give you
the money you need.

11:30.820 --> 11:34.041
I need $1.6 million.

11:34.084 --> 11:35.782
You sure you want
to make that bet?

11:35.825 --> 11:37.697
Always.

11:37.740 --> 11:39.133
The whole point
of having a lot of money

11:39.176 --> 11:42.614
is that you can play
however you want

11:42.658 --> 11:44.225
with whomever you want.

11:44.268 --> 11:49.404
♪♪

11:49.447 --> 11:54.626
♪♪

11:54.670 --> 11:55.627
Croupier: No more bets.

11:55.671 --> 11:57.499
[ Ball clinking ]

11:57.542 --> 12:00.458
♪♪

12:00.502 --> 12:03.113
Man:
Big money, big money, come on!

12:03.157 --> 12:10.294
♪♪

12:10.338 --> 12:13.602
It was so close.

12:13.645 --> 12:16.257
Let's sit down for a drink,
talk about what you need.

12:16.300 --> 12:18.346
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:18.389 --> 12:23.133
♪♪

12:23.177 --> 12:25.875
Scotch?

12:25.919 --> 12:27.834
It's the Sherry Oak 25.

12:27.877 --> 12:30.401
You remembered.

12:30.445 --> 12:33.796
My mind is like
a steel trap.

12:33.840 --> 12:35.450
For everything.

12:35.493 --> 12:37.452
Thank you for considering
the loan, Robert.

12:37.495 --> 12:40.368
We know it's a lot,
but we have collateral.

12:40.411 --> 12:42.544
Arman's vintage
1970 DeVille,

12:42.587 --> 12:43.980
the Caddy he just bought
last year --

12:44.024 --> 12:45.808
I can't pretend
those interest me.

12:45.852 --> 12:47.636
And there's also
the house.

12:49.812 --> 12:53.163
I want a piece
of the gun business.

12:53.207 --> 12:54.556
I hear
it was quite lucrative

12:54.599 --> 12:56.558
before Armando
landed behind bars.

12:56.601 --> 12:58.690
I-I can't speak
for my husband.

12:58.734 --> 13:01.432
Yet here you are,
negotiating his loan.

13:01.476 --> 13:04.740
And let me guess --
the cash to buy his freedom?

13:04.784 --> 13:06.829
Can't imagine him choosing
to stay behind bars

13:06.873 --> 13:08.526
over sharing a piece
of the pie.

13:08.570 --> 13:11.965
♪♪

13:12.008 --> 13:14.184
Good.

13:14.228 --> 13:16.621
I'll be in touch
as soon as the funds are ready.

13:18.145 --> 13:20.277
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:22.410 --> 13:23.933
Rat.

13:25.761 --> 13:28.851
Prisoner:
You better watch out.

13:28.895 --> 13:31.288
Prisoner #2:
Snitches get stitches.

13:37.599 --> 13:47.217
♪♪

13:47.261 --> 13:50.351
They say never judge a man
by his first round,

13:50.394 --> 13:54.790
but, man, you took
the crown, homey.

13:54.834 --> 13:56.400
Sit.

13:56.444 --> 13:59.273
♪♪

13:59.316 --> 14:00.535
You know, a lot of us
didn't think

14:00.578 --> 14:02.885
you were gonna
walk out of there.

14:02.929 --> 14:07.194
Lotta these fools, they lost
a lot of good wagers on you.

14:07.237 --> 14:10.545
But we're impressed.

14:10.588 --> 14:13.722
What do you want? Tu, hermano.

14:13.765 --> 14:17.204
We can always use someone
like you in our crew.

14:17.247 --> 14:20.598
And what are you
offering?

14:20.642 --> 14:23.906
Protection.

14:23.950 --> 14:26.735
You know we like to take care
of our own, que no?

14:26.778 --> 14:28.519
And word is, your boy,

14:28.563 --> 14:30.913
he's gonna make another
move on you again.

14:30.957 --> 14:33.394
Soon.

14:33.437 --> 14:37.050
Then it's not protection
I want.

14:37.093 --> 14:38.573
It's Hayak.

14:57.113 --> 14:58.375
One more.

14:58.419 --> 15:00.812
Mommy, I'm full.

15:00.856 --> 15:02.423
Really?Yes.

15:02.466 --> 15:03.946
Okay.

15:03.990 --> 15:05.382
Go brush your teeth then.

15:05.426 --> 15:08.559
No. Not till
he finishes his plate.

15:10.300 --> 15:12.868
We don't force him to eat
when he's not hungry anymore.

15:12.912 --> 15:14.348
Because you spoil him.

15:14.391 --> 15:16.393
I think I know
what's best for my son.

15:16.437 --> 15:18.830
Do you?

15:18.874 --> 15:20.049
Jacinto. Jacinto...

15:27.448 --> 15:30.320
You're all done here.

15:30.364 --> 15:32.932
Jaz, can you help Luca
get to bed, please?

15:32.975 --> 15:34.977
Sure.

15:35.021 --> 15:36.544
Come on, Luca.

15:36.587 --> 15:38.633
What kind of PJs do you want?
Spaceships or dinosaurs?

15:38.676 --> 15:40.548
Dinosaurs.

15:40.591 --> 15:44.117
What kind of wife
puts an APB on her husband?

15:44.160 --> 15:46.771
Thony:
Marco shouldn't have taken Luca.

15:46.815 --> 15:48.686
Everything I did,
I did for my son.

15:48.730 --> 15:52.995
Then why not come back to Manila
when the transplant was done?

15:53.039 --> 15:56.999
If Marco took Luca,
there must be good reason!

15:57.043 --> 16:00.524
No, Tatay,
it's not Thony's fault.

16:00.568 --> 16:03.527
Marco was a gambling addict,
and you know it.

16:03.571 --> 16:05.355
Okay, when he came to Vegas,
it got out of control.

16:05.399 --> 16:09.533
He even stole the money
Thony saved to save Luca's life.

16:09.577 --> 16:11.927
Marco was not at the motel
because of Thony.

16:11.971 --> 16:14.843
He was running from people
he owed money to.

16:14.886 --> 16:17.498
Marco started gambling
because she drove him to it.

16:17.541 --> 16:19.717
Oh, he made
his own decisions.

16:19.761 --> 16:21.110
No.

16:21.154 --> 16:24.809
You made him feel like
he was not enough.

16:24.853 --> 16:26.028
But he was.

16:26.072 --> 16:29.379
My son was enough!

16:29.423 --> 16:32.208
That's why we're going
to honor his wishes.

16:32.252 --> 16:34.036
[ Lola speaks Tagalog ]

16:34.080 --> 16:38.823
Marco did not want his son
to grow up Tago ng Tago.

16:40.173 --> 16:43.176
We're taking Luca back
to the Philippines with us.

16:43.219 --> 16:44.264
You can't do that.Mm-hmm.

16:44.307 --> 16:45.830
How can you agree to this?

16:45.874 --> 16:47.745
Luca belongs in Manila.[ Indistinct arguing ]

16:47.789 --> 16:49.747
I am his mother.This is why

16:49.791 --> 16:51.314
Marco turned out like this.Marco wanted this.

16:51.358 --> 16:53.577
Because of him! You spoiled him,
everything! It's --

16:53.621 --> 16:56.058
Shut up!
Everyone, stop!

17:03.022 --> 17:04.806
[ Door shuts ]

17:12.901 --> 17:14.685
[ Quietly ]
They're not taking Luca.

17:14.729 --> 17:16.948
They have no right.

17:16.992 --> 17:18.646
They're just upset.
I --

17:18.689 --> 17:21.431
I shouldn't have said anything
about Marco's gambling.

17:21.475 --> 17:24.478
No. They made their decision
before they even got here,

17:24.521 --> 17:28.786
with Marco just blaming me for
taking Luca all those months.

17:28.830 --> 17:30.005
Luca wants Chris
to tuck him in,

17:30.049 --> 17:31.702
but I can't
find him anywhere.

17:36.142 --> 17:42.452
♪♪

17:42.496 --> 17:48.719
♪♪

17:48.763 --> 17:50.504
Come on, Chris.

17:50.547 --> 17:52.941
♪♪

17:52.984 --> 17:54.986
Where are you?

17:55.030 --> 18:00.122
♪♪

18:00.166 --> 18:02.211
[ Tires screech ]

18:02.255 --> 18:07.347
♪♪

18:07.390 --> 18:09.349
[ Screams ]

18:09.392 --> 18:17.487
♪♪

18:17.531 --> 18:25.669
♪♪

18:25.713 --> 18:27.715
Chris.

18:27.758 --> 18:29.586
Chris.

18:29.630 --> 18:31.327
Chris, are you okay?

18:31.371 --> 18:32.981
Hey. Are you okay?

18:33.024 --> 18:35.114
Chris --
Yes, yes.

18:35.157 --> 18:36.376
Anak,I'm sorry.

18:36.419 --> 18:38.204
I'm sorry you had
to sit through that,

18:38.247 --> 18:40.728
but you gotta
come home, alright?

18:40.771 --> 18:42.164
No.
Come on.

18:42.208 --> 18:44.384
You lied, Mom.

18:44.427 --> 18:46.516
Uncle Marco didn't die
because of his gambling.

18:46.560 --> 18:47.909
He died because of me.

18:47.952 --> 18:49.171
No.
Yes.

18:49.215 --> 18:50.607
It's not your fault.

18:50.651 --> 18:52.870
Everything I said about Marco
was true.

18:52.914 --> 18:55.525
He was an addict.
His gambling hurt all of us.

18:55.569 --> 18:59.921
Nothing we do now
can change what he did

18:59.964 --> 19:03.316
or what happened.
Okay?

19:03.359 --> 19:07.058
All that matters now is --
is protecting you.

19:07.102 --> 19:10.105
♪♪

19:10.149 --> 19:12.063
I should just
turn myself in.

19:12.107 --> 19:13.717
No.

19:13.761 --> 19:16.677
No. You can't do that.
Okay?

19:16.720 --> 19:19.070
You can -- Hey, hey, hey,
look at me.

19:19.114 --> 19:24.554
You can never tell anyone
about this ever.

19:24.598 --> 19:28.384
You understand that, huh?

19:28.428 --> 19:29.559
Come on.

19:29.603 --> 19:33.302
Means we just
keep lying, right?

19:33.346 --> 19:35.086
To everyone.

19:35.130 --> 19:41.528
♪♪

19:45.967 --> 19:47.795
[ Indistinct conversations ]

19:47.838 --> 19:49.188
Arman:
I know his schedule.

19:49.231 --> 19:52.103
Who protects him.
How he thinks.

19:52.147 --> 19:55.759
You tell me where and when,
we'll take care of him, homes.

19:55.803 --> 19:58.327
No, I'll take care of Hayak.

19:58.371 --> 20:01.417
I just need him alone.

20:01.461 --> 20:03.289
He conducts business
at the laundry.

20:03.332 --> 20:05.987
Isolate him there.

20:06.030 --> 20:10.252
♪♪

20:10.296 --> 20:12.733
Yeah, we can
make that happen,

20:12.776 --> 20:14.169
but that kind of service,

20:14.213 --> 20:17.607
it's gonna require more
than your canteen money.

20:17.651 --> 20:19.740
What do you need?

20:19.783 --> 20:22.133
Yo, I got a girl and a baby
on the outside.

20:22.177 --> 20:23.961
Diapers ain't cheap,
you feel me?

20:24.005 --> 20:25.572
Understood.

20:25.615 --> 20:28.052
I'll have my wife send out
a payment to your girl.

20:28.096 --> 20:29.576
Yeah, alright.

20:29.619 --> 20:31.230
[ Buzzer in distance ]

20:31.273 --> 20:33.623
♪♪

20:33.667 --> 20:37.540
Yo, uh, Arman...

20:37.584 --> 20:39.455
you sure
you ready for this now?

20:39.499 --> 20:42.415
[ Indistinct conversations ]

20:42.458 --> 20:45.200
♪♪

20:45.244 --> 20:46.854
I'm ready.

20:46.897 --> 20:52.294
♪♪

20:52.338 --> 20:55.558
No, I don't like it.
It's itchy.

20:55.602 --> 20:58.126
Come here, my love.

20:58.169 --> 21:01.477
Lolo and Lola brought this
Barongespecially for you.

21:01.521 --> 21:04.959
Don't you want to look nice
for Daddy's service?

21:05.002 --> 21:06.308
Yeah?

21:06.352 --> 21:08.179
No, I just want Daddy.

21:08.223 --> 21:11.487
Luca, please.

21:11.531 --> 21:13.663
Lolo: Sandali, sandali.

21:13.707 --> 21:18.320
♪♪

21:18.364 --> 21:20.322
You know, Luca,

21:20.366 --> 21:23.630
this Barongis very special.

21:23.673 --> 21:25.284
Your Tataywore it

21:25.327 --> 21:30.027
the day that Tita Fi
was baptized.

21:30.071 --> 21:32.029
He picked it himself,

21:32.073 --> 21:35.250
said it was for "Fi Fi" day.

21:35.294 --> 21:38.253
Now you can wear it

21:38.297 --> 21:41.343
for Tatay'sday, okay?

21:41.387 --> 21:42.953
Okay, Lolo.

21:42.997 --> 21:52.354
♪♪

21:52.398 --> 21:54.313
[ Cellphone ringing ]

21:54.356 --> 22:02.712
♪♪

22:02.756 --> 22:04.366
Nadia:
We've got a problem.

22:04.410 --> 22:06.020
The Feds have been
watching me all morning,

22:06.063 --> 22:09.066
so I can't meet Kamdar
to get the money to the judge.

22:09.110 --> 22:10.851
You have to.

22:10.894 --> 22:12.243
I can't.

22:12.287 --> 22:14.158
We're about to leave
for my husband's funeral.

22:14.202 --> 22:15.725
And you're gonna handle it

22:15.769 --> 22:17.814
so I don't have to go
to myhusband's funeral.

22:17.858 --> 22:21.514
♪♪

22:21.557 --> 22:23.254
[ Sighs ]

22:23.298 --> 22:26.040
Fi, I need you
to cover for me.

22:26.083 --> 22:28.738
What? Where the hell
are you going?

22:28.782 --> 22:31.088
Just one last thing.

22:31.132 --> 22:32.742
Please.

22:32.786 --> 22:33.874
Seriously?

22:33.917 --> 22:35.745
Now? Come on, Thony.

22:35.789 --> 22:37.530
I really don't know what it is
about you and this guy,

22:37.573 --> 22:39.793
but you're about
to bury your husband.

22:39.836 --> 22:42.491
You didn't see
what Hayak did to him.

22:42.535 --> 22:43.840
Please.

22:43.884 --> 22:46.277
Just one thing,
and I'll meet you there.

22:46.321 --> 22:48.932
♪♪

22:48.976 --> 22:52.936
Just tell them I-I went
for flowers or something.

22:52.980 --> 22:55.678
Fine, but, hey,
you have less than an hour.

22:55.722 --> 22:57.288
Don't be late.

22:57.332 --> 22:59.682
♪♪

22:59.726 --> 23:02.032
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

23:06.950 --> 23:08.561
[ Knock on door ]

23:11.302 --> 23:12.826
[ Sighs ]Hey. Hey, whoa, whoa,

23:12.869 --> 23:14.654
whoa, whoa. Maya, Maya, look.
I just want to --

23:14.697 --> 23:17.091
I just want to talk.
No, Garrett. You can't be here.

23:17.134 --> 23:18.788
Why? What's wrong?

23:18.832 --> 23:20.703
Are you -- Are you safe?

23:24.968 --> 23:27.580
♪♪

23:27.623 --> 23:29.146
Maya:
What do you want, Garrett?

23:29.190 --> 23:32.019
I heard you're
dealing for Cortez now.

23:32.062 --> 23:33.977
How the hell
did that happen?

23:34.021 --> 23:36.719
Well, you pushed me, pushing me
closer and closer to him,

23:36.763 --> 23:39.156
and, what, now you have
a problem with it?

23:39.200 --> 23:41.420
Come on, Garrett.
What'd you expect?

23:41.463 --> 23:42.986
You disappeared
over a year ago.

23:43.030 --> 23:44.118
No word, no explanation.

23:44.161 --> 23:45.946
No, no, I'm sorry, Maya.No.

23:45.989 --> 23:49.428
You don't just get to show up
out of the blue and say that.

23:49.471 --> 23:50.864
I had no choice, Maya.

23:50.907 --> 23:54.215
They pulled me
off the case.

23:54.258 --> 23:55.738
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

23:55.782 --> 23:58.001
'Cause that's
all I was to you.

23:58.045 --> 23:59.655
Another case, right?

23:59.699 --> 24:03.006
That's not true.

24:03.050 --> 24:06.183
I'm here because
I want to help you.

24:06.227 --> 24:07.620
You know, if you need money
or a place to go --

24:07.663 --> 24:09.926
No, you know what I don't need
is your sympathy

24:09.970 --> 24:12.494
and your stupid apologies.

24:12.538 --> 24:14.148
I'm fine without you,

24:14.191 --> 24:15.541
better off, honestly.

24:15.584 --> 24:17.847
[ Men shouting in distance ]

24:17.891 --> 24:21.372
♪♪

24:21.416 --> 24:24.245
Expecting someone?

24:24.288 --> 24:25.942
[ Sighs ]

24:25.986 --> 24:33.341
♪♪

24:33.384 --> 24:35.735
Can you just go?

24:35.778 --> 24:37.040
That's what
you're good at, right?

24:37.084 --> 24:38.694
Come here. Look at me.

24:38.738 --> 24:41.088
Hey, look at me.
Just tell me what's going on.

24:41.131 --> 24:45.701
♪♪

24:45.745 --> 24:48.617
Uh, just don't --Hey.

24:48.661 --> 24:51.011
Okay, no, I'm sorry, alright?
I'm sorry.

24:51.054 --> 25:00.890
♪♪

25:00.934 --> 25:02.544
Wait, you're sleeping
with him now?

25:02.588 --> 25:04.111
Cortez?

25:04.154 --> 25:05.765
You gotta be kidding.

25:05.808 --> 25:08.071
Huh?

25:08.115 --> 25:09.812
You know he's dangerous.

25:09.856 --> 25:11.858
Maya, you know this.

25:11.901 --> 25:13.599
[ Cellphone ringing ]

25:13.642 --> 25:20.431
♪♪

25:20.475 --> 25:22.085
Maya: Don't come back.

25:22.129 --> 25:24.044
[ Cellphone continues ringing ]

25:24.087 --> 25:30.224
♪♪

25:30.267 --> 25:32.487
Yeah?We've been tailing Nadia
all morning,

25:32.531 --> 25:35.577
and she just left the bank that
holds the deed to her house.

25:35.621 --> 25:37.187
Alright. It's on.

25:37.231 --> 25:41.104
♪♪

25:41.148 --> 25:43.672
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:43.716 --> 25:50.766
♪♪

25:50.810 --> 25:57.817
♪♪

25:57.860 --> 26:00.863
Thony:
I'm here to see Mr. Kamdar.

26:00.907 --> 26:03.300
Mrs. Morales sent me.

26:03.344 --> 26:06.129
I believe she called.

26:06.173 --> 26:07.653
This way.

26:07.696 --> 26:15.269
♪♪

26:15.312 --> 26:22.798
♪♪

26:22.842 --> 26:24.583
Robert: Yeah?

26:24.626 --> 26:33.853
♪♪

26:33.896 --> 26:35.637
Mr. Kamdar.

26:35.681 --> 26:40.033
♪♪

26:40.076 --> 26:41.991
Robert:
You checked she wasn't wired?

26:42.035 --> 26:44.211
♪♪

26:44.254 --> 26:46.517
Not yet.

26:46.561 --> 26:49.042
Okay.

26:49.085 --> 26:50.739
I've got it.

26:52.523 --> 26:55.657
I've never cared very much
for last-minute changes.

26:55.701 --> 27:00.836
♪♪

27:00.880 --> 27:03.665
Where's Nadia?

27:03.709 --> 27:05.536
She was being watched.

27:05.580 --> 27:08.365
That's why
s-she sent me instead.

27:08.409 --> 27:11.107
♪♪

27:11.151 --> 27:15.198
You understand I don't trust
anyone I don't know.

27:15.242 --> 27:18.462
So I'd like you to do
something for me.

27:18.506 --> 27:20.029
Strip.

27:20.073 --> 27:24.817
♪♪

27:24.860 --> 27:27.689
Don't worry.
They can't see in.

27:27.733 --> 27:37.046
♪♪

27:37.090 --> 27:46.403
♪♪

27:46.447 --> 27:48.014
Let me help.

27:48.057 --> 27:57.414
♪♪

27:57.458 --> 28:06.728
♪♪

28:06.772 --> 28:09.078
What exactly is
your relationship to Nadia?

28:09.122 --> 28:11.472
I-I work for them
as a cleaning lady.

28:11.515 --> 28:14.040
♪♪

28:14.083 --> 28:17.783
Sometimes, they send me
to do other things.

28:17.826 --> 28:20.437
♪♪

28:20.481 --> 28:24.006
That's a lot
of responsibility

28:24.050 --> 28:25.921
for a maid.

28:25.965 --> 28:27.749
♪♪

28:27.793 --> 28:30.665
No one pays attention
to the cleaning lady.

28:30.709 --> 28:33.146
♪♪

28:33.189 --> 28:34.756
It's clean.

28:34.800 --> 28:38.325
♪♪

28:38.368 --> 28:41.328
Thank you
for indulging me.

28:41.371 --> 28:42.938
Please get dressed.

28:42.982 --> 28:50.467
♪♪

28:50.511 --> 28:52.948
[ Spits ]

28:52.992 --> 28:54.558
Don't ever
bring anyone back here

28:54.602 --> 28:56.822
without checking them first.

28:56.865 --> 29:02.653
♪♪

29:02.697 --> 29:05.656
Oh, dear.

29:05.700 --> 29:07.310
Look at this mess.

29:10.183 --> 29:12.054
But you're a cleaning lady,
aren't you?

29:12.098 --> 29:14.796
♪♪

29:14.840 --> 29:16.798
How long would it take
to clean that up?

29:16.842 --> 29:20.323
♪♪

29:20.367 --> 29:23.065
Uh, n-n--

29:23.109 --> 29:24.719
I'm kidding.[ Gasps ]

29:24.763 --> 29:28.505
♪♪

29:28.549 --> 29:31.987
You're not dressed to clean.

29:32.031 --> 29:35.425
I'll get you Nadia's money,
and then

29:35.469 --> 29:37.297
you're free to go.

29:37.340 --> 29:44.217
♪♪

29:48.525 --> 29:53.704
♪♪

29:53.748 --> 29:58.884
♪♪

29:58.927 --> 30:01.843
You remind me of him.

30:01.887 --> 30:04.106
So handsome.

30:04.150 --> 30:06.935
So smart.

30:06.979 --> 30:10.765
He was such a good boy.

30:10.809 --> 30:13.072
Hey, uh, Chris?

30:13.115 --> 30:14.987
Why don't you go
help your sister

30:15.030 --> 30:17.250
finish setting up
inside, huh?

30:17.293 --> 30:19.818
No.
You stay here with me

30:19.861 --> 30:22.864
to greet the guests,
Anak,huh?

30:22.908 --> 30:24.997
♪♪

30:25.040 --> 30:26.737
Hey.

30:26.781 --> 30:28.565
Where's Thony?

30:28.609 --> 30:30.785
She just went
to go get some flowers.

30:30.829 --> 30:32.091
Now?

30:32.134 --> 30:34.093
I'm sure she'll be back
in a minute.

30:34.136 --> 30:36.138
Uh, uh, there's Samentha.

30:36.182 --> 30:38.401
I'm just gonna thank her
for the food.

30:38.445 --> 30:44.016
♪♪

30:44.059 --> 30:46.148
Prison doctor:
Couple of stitches popped.

30:46.192 --> 30:47.584
That's all.

30:47.628 --> 30:49.848
Butterfly closure
oughta do it.

30:49.891 --> 30:51.893
I think I'm gonna need
a bigger bandage.

30:51.937 --> 30:54.069
Blood seeped through
the last one.

30:54.113 --> 30:56.332
No need for that.
This'll help.

31:00.902 --> 31:08.431
♪♪

31:08.475 --> 31:16.091
♪♪

31:16.135 --> 31:18.180
Man:
Can I get hands over here, stat?

31:18.224 --> 31:23.969
♪♪

31:24.012 --> 31:25.318
Garrett: Alright, I got her.

31:25.361 --> 31:27.537
Nadia's rolling in now.

31:27.581 --> 31:29.931
My bet, she's got the bribe
in her bag.

31:29.975 --> 31:31.628
You got eyes on Judge Tuckerson?

31:31.672 --> 31:34.762
Judge is in his usual spot,
usual time.

31:34.805 --> 31:37.243
And that is why I like
to stay unpredictable.

31:37.286 --> 31:38.853
No one can pin me down.

31:38.897 --> 31:41.812
Unfortunately,
neither could your wife.

31:41.856 --> 31:43.205
Ouch.

31:44.903 --> 31:47.818
Alright,
team's in place.

31:47.862 --> 31:49.385
And here we go.

31:49.429 --> 31:55.435
♪♪

31:55.478 --> 31:57.393
Bonjour, Madame Morales.
Comment allez vous?

31:57.437 --> 31:59.047
Je vais bien, merci.
Et vous?

31:59.091 --> 32:01.354
Tres bien.
Uh moment, s'il vous plait.

32:01.397 --> 32:09.188
♪♪

32:09.231 --> 32:10.493
Russo:
And the maitre d' is heading

32:10.537 --> 32:12.669
towards Judge Tuckerson now.

32:12.713 --> 32:21.940
♪♪

32:21.983 --> 32:22.984
What the hell?

32:23.028 --> 32:25.160
What? What's going on?

32:25.204 --> 32:31.427
♪♪

32:31.471 --> 32:33.995
Talk to me, Russo.
You there?

32:34.039 --> 32:36.824
Do not get out of your car.Why?

32:36.867 --> 32:39.000
It looks like he's bringing her
a takeout bag.

32:39.044 --> 32:40.262
She's coming back out.

32:40.306 --> 32:42.047
It's a bust.

32:42.090 --> 32:43.396
Maitre d': Voilà, madame.

32:43.439 --> 32:45.485
Merci. Au revoir. Au revoir.

32:45.528 --> 32:48.531
Wait a minute. So th-- This
wasn't a hand-off of the bribe?

32:48.575 --> 32:50.011
No.

32:50.055 --> 32:52.274
They knew
we were watching.

32:52.318 --> 32:53.972
It was a decoy.

32:54.015 --> 32:56.235
Alright, it still could be
happening somewhere else.

32:56.278 --> 33:02.067
♪♪

33:02.110 --> 33:07.942
♪♪

33:07.986 --> 33:09.639
Mr. Stephens?

33:09.683 --> 33:11.685
Stephens: I'll take care
of these. Thank you.

33:11.728 --> 33:13.687
Thank you.

33:13.730 --> 33:16.385
Oh, my God. You made it.
Everybody's been asking for you.

33:16.429 --> 33:20.520
Yeah, I-I'm sorry
I couldn't get here sooner.

33:20.563 --> 33:23.392
I-It's okay.
You're here now.

33:23.436 --> 33:31.922
♪♪

33:31.966 --> 33:40.409
♪♪

33:40.453 --> 33:42.542
It's time, Thony.

33:42.585 --> 33:49.462
♪♪

33:49.505 --> 33:56.425
♪♪

33:56.469 --> 34:03.389
♪♪

34:03.432 --> 34:06.392
Stephens:
Judge Tuckerson.

34:06.435 --> 34:09.264
You sure no one saw you
or followed you here?

34:09.308 --> 34:11.440
All clear, Your Honor.

34:11.484 --> 34:12.833
It's all here.

34:12.876 --> 34:17.533
♪♪

34:17.577 --> 34:19.187
Thank you.

34:19.231 --> 34:24.888
♪♪

34:36.813 --> 34:38.815
I'm sorry, my man.

34:38.859 --> 34:41.470
I really didn't want it
to go down like this.

34:41.514 --> 34:46.084
But in this house,
highest bidder wins.

34:46.127 --> 34:49.261
♪♪

34:49.304 --> 34:51.263
As I always said,

34:51.306 --> 34:55.745
if you want things done right,
do it yourself.

34:55.789 --> 34:58.661
It doesn't have to go on
like this, Hayak.

34:58.705 --> 35:01.186
You and I can both
walk out of here alive.

35:01.229 --> 35:03.101
Too late for that.

35:03.144 --> 35:05.233
♪♪

35:05.277 --> 35:07.888
[ Both grunting ]

35:07.931 --> 35:17.724
♪♪

35:17.767 --> 35:27.603
♪♪

35:27.647 --> 35:37.439
♪♪

35:37.483 --> 35:39.180
[ Chuckles ]

35:39.224 --> 35:46.535
♪♪

35:46.579 --> 35:53.934
♪♪

35:53.977 --> 36:01.246
♪♪

36:01.289 --> 36:04.031
[ Gasping ]

36:09.950 --> 36:13.127
It won't be long now.

36:13.171 --> 36:16.174
Your heart will seize,
and it'll be done.

36:16.217 --> 36:20.003
I always loved you
more than my own son.

36:22.180 --> 36:31.232
♪♪

36:31.276 --> 36:33.452
[ Gasping stops ]

36:33.495 --> 36:38.326
♪♪

36:38.370 --> 36:41.024
[ Door opens ]

36:41.068 --> 36:45.377
♪♪

36:50.599 --> 36:52.558
♪♪

36:52.601 --> 36:54.037
Luca's asking for you.

36:54.081 --> 36:56.257
Again.

36:56.301 --> 36:58.390
I-I can't do this
right now.

36:58.433 --> 37:01.480
Just -- Just -- Just get
Auntie T or something.

37:01.523 --> 37:03.786
He doesn't want his mom
right now. He wants you.

37:03.830 --> 37:06.267
[ Breathing heavily ]

37:06.311 --> 37:08.574
Come on, Chris.
He just lost his dad,

37:08.617 --> 37:10.053
and you're the closest thing
he has to that,

37:10.097 --> 37:12.795
so whatever
you're feeling right now,

37:12.839 --> 37:15.058
it can't be worse
than Luca.

37:15.102 --> 37:21.456
♪♪

37:21.500 --> 37:27.941
♪♪

37:27.984 --> 37:29.595
Nay.

37:32.337 --> 37:36.689
I'm sorry I said those things
about Marco's gambling.

37:36.732 --> 37:39.822
I-I didn't want that to be
your last memory of him.

37:43.043 --> 37:45.698
Your Tatayand I made...

37:45.741 --> 37:50.050
a lot of mistakes
raising the two of you.

37:50.093 --> 37:53.358
We spoiled Marco, but...

37:53.401 --> 37:57.057
that doesn't mean
we love you less.

37:57.100 --> 38:00.669
We just thought
that you were stronger.

38:00.713 --> 38:04.325
It didn't mean
I didn't need you, Nanay.

38:04.369 --> 38:07.633
I know.

38:07.676 --> 38:10.592
But look what you've done.

38:10.636 --> 38:12.681
♪♪

38:12.725 --> 38:15.162
Coming here,

38:15.205 --> 38:17.947
raising two kids

38:17.991 --> 38:22.300
in a new country, alone.

38:22.343 --> 38:24.084
You're a good mom.

38:27.087 --> 38:34.529
♪♪

38:34.573 --> 38:39.665
I understand why Thony and Luca
would like to stay with you.

38:39.708 --> 38:43.059
But your Tatay,he --

38:43.103 --> 38:45.714
he has other ideas.

38:46.715 --> 38:48.804
[ Washer door opens ]

38:48.848 --> 38:50.806
[ Washer door shuts ]

38:54.288 --> 38:58.074
I know you think you know
what's best for your son.

38:58.118 --> 39:00.903
I used to feel that, too.

39:00.947 --> 39:05.473
But when you bury a child...

39:05.517 --> 39:07.562
you feel like
you failed them.

39:16.963 --> 39:19.357
It's something

39:19.400 --> 39:23.796
most parents
never want to imagine.

39:23.839 --> 39:26.102
I understand,

39:26.146 --> 39:32.326
because I had to face that
possibility every day, Tatay,

39:32.370 --> 39:36.809
and that's why I did
what I did to save Luca.

39:36.852 --> 39:39.551
That was necessary,
I know.

39:39.594 --> 39:44.294
And now Marco will
live on in Luca.

39:44.338 --> 39:47.646
But you see, that boy

39:47.689 --> 39:52.128
is the only thing
I have left of my son.

39:52.172 --> 39:55.480
Yes.
But he's not your son.

39:55.523 --> 39:57.960
He's mine.

39:58.004 --> 40:03.096
And we are making a life here
with Fiona and the kids.

40:03.139 --> 40:10.973
♪♪

40:11.017 --> 40:18.807
♪♪

40:18.851 --> 40:26.641
♪♪

40:26.685 --> 40:31.124
The prayer for the dead asks God

40:31.167 --> 40:34.344
to help the soul
of Marco De La Rosa

40:34.388 --> 40:37.913
for whom we make this novena.

40:37.957 --> 40:40.002
Let us kneel.

40:40.046 --> 40:45.181
♪♪

40:45.225 --> 40:49.098
We entrust our son
to your mercy.

40:49.142 --> 40:50.404
Please forgive his sins,

40:50.448 --> 40:53.189
especially those
that are unconfessed.

40:53.233 --> 40:55.191
♪♪

40:55.235 --> 41:00.327
May your perpetual light
shine upon him.

41:00.370 --> 41:04.984
Now he is freed,
through your blood on the cross,

41:05.027 --> 41:07.421
through the blows to your face,

41:07.465 --> 41:12.513
and through the crown of your
thorns that pierced your head,

41:12.557 --> 41:16.212
deliver him from all evil,

41:16.256 --> 41:19.825
from the rigor of injustice,

41:19.868 --> 41:22.871
from the torment of conscience,

41:22.915 --> 41:26.048
and from all darkness.

41:26.092 --> 41:28.311
Welcome him into Paradise,

41:28.355 --> 41:31.010
where there will be
no more sorrow,

41:31.053 --> 41:34.187
no more weeping or pain.

41:34.230 --> 41:37.930
Give him the blessings
of the life to come

41:37.973 --> 41:42.456
as he enters into
the kingdom of peace and light.

41:47.722 --> 41:56.905
♪♪

41:56.949 --> 42:06.262
♪♪

42:06.306 --> 42:15.533
♪♪
